pageContext.claim: “We're working with the state and local authorities to comb through hours of video tape, identifying arrest suspects; and prosecute lawbreakers. We've already got over 300 in jail, and we have tremendous evidence.”
pageContext.analysis: As of Oct. 20, the federal government had arrested more than 300 people — 286 of which are defendants in federal cases — according to an AP tally. Some of those arrested do identify as part of left-wing activist groups, but others are part of right wing groups and not all of which are in jail.
